sequenceDiagram
    participant Kafka as Kafka Broker<br/>9096/TCP SASL_SSL
    participant Processor as Kafka Processor<br/>(Python CLI - Build-Time)
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>data/ directory
    participant Build as Container Build<br/>(Konflux)
    participant Registry as Image Registry
    participant Operator as model-registry-operator
    participant InitC as Init Container<br/>(Data Image)
    participant Volume as Shared Volume<br/>/app/benchmarks
    participant Catalog as model-catalog<br/>Main Container

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Kafka, FS: Flow 1: Benchmark Data Ingestion (Build-Time / Offline)
        Kafka->>Processor: Consume messages<br/>SASL_SSL (SCRAM-SHA-512)<br/>Topics: dev.aihub-public-Model, etc.
        Note over Processor: Detect entity type<br/>(topic name / field heuristics)
        Note over Processor: Apply transforms:<br/>- OverallAccuracyTransform<br/>- HardwareConfigurationTransform
        Processor->>FS: Write structured files<br/>provider.json, metadata.json<br/>performance.ndjson<br/>evaluations.ndjson<br/>validation.ndjson<br/>manifest.json
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over FS, Registry: Flow 2: Container Image Build
        FS->>Build: COPY data/ → /app/benchmarks
        Build->>Registry: Push image<br/>odh-model-performance-data-rhel9
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Operator, Catalog: Flow 3: Benchmark Data Serving (Runtime)
        Operator->>Operator: Manage model-catalog Deployment<br/>Inject init container reference
        Note over InitC: Pod starts
        InitC->>Volume: Populate /app/benchmarks<br/>(volume mount)
        Note over InitC: Init container completes
        Catalog->>Volume: Read benchmark data<br/>at startup (volume mount)
        Note over Catalog: Serve benchmark data<br/>to model catalog users
    end
